The police in Owerri, Imo State, have arrested one of the suspects who allegedly attacked one of its stations in Orji, Owerri North Local Government Area. Police spokesman in the state, SP Bala Elkana, said in a statement, that the suspect was arrested in his hideout at Ikeduru LGA following an intelligence report. According to him, at about 9.am, the command in a joint operation with Ikeduru Police Division, arrested one The police spokesman said that the suspect, Chukwumakpa Henry (32), was alleged to have participated in the attack on Orji Police Station on 25th May, 2021 and other heinous crimes, stressing that he confessed to the commission of the offence and other violent crimes in the recent past. He further said, “Some grammes of a substance suspected to be cocaine were recovered from him. He confessed dealing in illicit and hard drugs as a means of subsistence. Investigation is ongoing while effort is being intensified to arrest other gang members.” 